    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Using a conjoint analysis based on cases in Japan, this study attempts to identify a preferable social strategic combination of \u201cWho is vaccinated, who is not, who waits.\u201d The analysis shows that the most desirable choice is a \u201cwait-and-see\u201d strategy, allowing for a risk assessment of side effects. We also find that subjects who recalled blood relatives as their familiar entities tend to prefer a \u201cwait-and-see\u201d strategy for themselves and their blood relatives.</jats:p>",
